cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with deep learning on graphs and graph convolutional neural networks. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a new approach for learning on directed graphs. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as graph convolutional networks have been applied to image data. It may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as graphs are commonly used to model social networks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the development of a neural network architecture.
